Black varies from opening theory, with this awkward move. Immediately one can notice the weak white squares around the black king. These should be attacked immediately.
So I develop, aiming at some weak white squares.
I encourage trading off black's white squared bishop for my knight, for without it, his weakened white squares are even less defended.
